.vscode/**
src/**
test/**
out/**
# Dev-only fixtures and outputs that bloated the .vsix to 1200 files / 17.7 MB:
# test-ux ships ~10 MB of UX screenshots, and reports/ ships dozens of 1 MB+
# i18n translation-audit .md files. Neither is loaded at runtime, and the audit
# reports carry the same high-entropy translated strings that already tripped
# Open VSX's secret scanner via scripts/ (below).
test-ux/**
reports/**
# Bundled output ships as dist/extension.js; the matching source map is dev-only.
**/*.map
# Build-time tooling only (i18n MT pipeline + caches). Never loaded at runtime —
# runtime locales live in src/i18n/locales and are bundled into out/ by esbuild.
# Shipping scripts/ also leaked the MT cache (mt_strings.json), whose high-entropy
# translated strings trip Open VSX's secret scanner and block publication.
scripts/**
tsconfig.json
node_modules/**
.gitignore
package-lock.json
esbuild.js
*.vsix
# Bare *.md only matches the package root; nested reports/*.md leaked into the
# .vsix until reports/** (above) excluded them. Use **/*.md to drop docs at any
# depth, then re-include the two top-level files the Marketplace listing needs.
**/*.md
!README.md
!CHANGELOG.md
!media/**
